1
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:24,600
<i>I'm going out of town.</i>
<i>Not sure when I'll be back.</i>

2
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,600
<i>Don't worry.</i>

3
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:28,240
<i>Just spend your time working for me.</i>
<i>Go live your life.</i>

4
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:29,720
<i>When you finish the job,</i>

5
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,680
<i>you'll get my shares for sure.</i>

6
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,600
I've set the profit margin too low.

7
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:39,000
I should make it 100%.

8
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:41,680
Move your bag off the laptop.

9
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,320
Can't you see something's there?

10
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,840
It's a light bag. It's fine sitting there.

11
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,000
What's the big deal?

12
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,840
That's exactly why you're so shallow.

13
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:55,280
You want to be an influencer,
but you don't know what an influencer is.

14
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:57,960
We're not even close enough
for you to talk to me like that.

15
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,200
Learn some manners.

16
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:02,480
And the person who puts their bag
on someone else's laptop has manners?

17
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,560
Tell me honestly,

18
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,880
have you ever done anything useful
for the family?

19
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,800
I'm doing it, Dad!

20
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:14,080
If I had known that you were going to ruin
the family business,

21
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:16,280
I would've started saving
since primary school.

22
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,000
But no one knew back then.

23
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,680
How was I supposed to prepare in time?

24
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:35,080
I'm tired of arguing with you like this.

25
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:40,240
Just give me the money.
One or 200,000 would be fine.

26
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
You stand there yelling at me nonstop,

27
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,240
yet you're asking for money.

28
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:50,040
You think I'll give it to you? Dream on.

29
00:02:57,040 --> 00:02:58,480
-Pound!
-Pound!

30
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:00,680
I asked you for help,

31
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,400
but you never cared.
You never supported me at all.

32
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,080
If I ask nicely
and you won't give it to me,

33
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,280
I'll just get it myself.

34
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:10,520
But I'm telling you,
if I find it, I'm taking it all.

35
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,680
-Pound!
-Wait, Pound!

36
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,280
-Pound, where are you going?
-Pound!

37
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,440
-Don't!
-Dad!

38
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,800
Pound! Give me my money back.

39
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:40,120
-No! Your money is my money too.
-Give it back!

40
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,640
-Give it back!
-You're responsible for me.

41
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,920
You brought me into this world.

42
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,680
-Pound!
-No!

43
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:46,280
No! Ouch!

44
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,680
-Pound!
-Give me my money back.

45
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:49,640
-Pound!
-No!

46
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,720
-Dad!
-I told you to let go!

47
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:53,520
-No! This is my money!
-Please stop it!

48
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:56,000
-Don't fight anymore!
-That's enough!

49
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:58,080
I told you to stop!

50
00:03:58,800 --> 00:03:59,880
If you don't stop,

51
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:02,280
-I'll kill myself.
-Mom!

52
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,280
-Mom!
-Mom!

53
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:05,240
-Mom!
-Mom!

54
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,080
Calm down.

55
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,360
Give the money to him.

56
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:12,040
I told you to give the money to him!

57
00:04:15,720 --> 00:04:18,480
Take my share and give it to him.

58
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,800
He can do whatever he wants with it.

59
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:27,200
But this is our last bit of money.

60
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,960
Just give it to him.

61
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,560
I said give it to him!

62
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,000
Mom!

63
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:37,960
Mom!

64
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,240
Take it!

65
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,600
And don't ever come near me again.

66
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,440
Why are you so selfish?

67
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,720
Do you even know what you just did?

68
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,240
I know.

69
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,400
But there was no other way.

70
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,640
If there was, I wouldn't have done it.

71
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:36,240
That's not true.

72
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:39,280
People always have a choice.

73
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:43,320
A choice to do or not do something.

74
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,720
But you chose to do it.

75
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,880
You have to take responsibility
for what you chose.

76
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,960
I'll take responsibility. Don't worry.

77
00:05:57,680 --> 00:06:00,400
No matter how much
everyone hates me or curses me,

78
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,680
what I did, I did it for the family.

79
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:08,880
I'm going to make our family rich again.

80
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:11,360
The money Dad gave me today has to grow.

81
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,120
He won't regret giving it to me.

82
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:39,480
<i>Do you know money can change people?</i>

83
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:42,360
<i>It can turn a good person into a bad one.</i>

84
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:45,400
And it can also turn
a bad person into a good one.

85
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:47,480
What do you mean?

86
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:50,920
Don't you see? Those people who cheat,

87
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,520
deal drugs, or run shady businesses,

88
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:56,040
they donate a million or two
and suddenly they're good people.

89
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,040
-That's true.
-Right?

90
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,680
Oh. And about you funding Cent
to make the app,

91
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,560
why did you do that?

92
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:07,680
If the money I invest

93
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,040
helps my son learn how to live,

94
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,560
enjoy life,

95
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,200
and also learn to help others,

96
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:19,760
then isn't it worth the investment?

97
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,480
Yes.

98
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,480
Sorry.

99
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,240
Sorry I'm late.

100
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,920
I stayed up late last night,
helping a friend with some design--

101
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,720
Helping a friend again?

102
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:45,840
My friend asked for help. I'm sorry.

103
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,680
Stop talking. You're wasting time.
Go. Move.

104
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,520
Yes.

105
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,960
TAXI

106
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:39,000
Is this really all the equipment I need?

107
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:42,159
No wonder anyone can become a YouTuber.

108
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:44,880
But your content

109
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,200
has to be good too.

110
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,080
Have you thought
about what you're going to do?

111
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:52,160
After the story
about moving on from Peace,

112
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,920
what are you going to do next?

113
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,760
I was thinking lifestyle stuff,
food, travel,

114
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,080
fashion, and simple beauty stuff.

115
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:03,240
But these days,
beauty content is so oversaturated.

116
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:07,480
Some channels even switch
to travel and food instead.

117
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,160
After doing my research,

118
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,440
I'm kind of scared too.

119
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,800
So many talented people
with high production quality.

120
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,680
Hey, don't be scared.

121
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,800
You've got your own style.

122
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:25,000
Be confident in yourself.
You'll figure it out.

123
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:29,440
And the people who like you
will start following you.

124
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:34,040
At least you've got me.

125
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:54,360
Yuan, that's so sweet.

126
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:55,440
Yeah.

127
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,000
Yeah, you're right.

128
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:01,480
I still have my friends who follow me,

129
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:03,640
like my posts, and support me.

130
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,240
Thank you, Yuan, my dear friend.

131
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,480
Yeah.

132
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:16,440
Honestly, you give
better advice than Cent.

133
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,160
I shouldn't have wasted time
getting scolded by him.

134
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:23,200
Just thinking about it
makes me so mad. I'm so mad!

135
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,200
Talking about it just ruins my mood.

136
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,960
I can't close it.

137
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:35,160
I'll close it for you.

138
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,160
Why are you so mad?

139
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,600
-Hey.
-Huh?

140
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,720
About your moving on video…

141
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,080
Have you really gotten over Peace?

142
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,280
Honestly,

143
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,720
I still feel a bit empty, you know?

144
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:02,280
We were together for years.
Losing someone like that isn't easy.

145
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:05,760
But luckily, I'm not the type
who likes being sad.

146
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:09,280
When I start feeling down,
I go do something to distract myself.

147
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:12,600
So now, I think I'm doing better.

148
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,720
I'm really happy for you.

149
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:22,360
Thanks for worrying about me.

150
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:25,880
What about you?
How are things? Any love life?

151
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:30,400
I've known you since kindergarten,
and I've never seen you with a girlfriend.

152
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:33,080
Are you just not telling me?

153
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,320
Yuan!

154
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:38,120
Oh? You went quiet there. What is it?

155
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:39,920
No.

156
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,280
I don't have a girlfriend or anything.

157
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:45,360
You're acting so suspicious. Really?

158
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:48,000
Really.

159
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,960
I don't really want to think
about relationships yet.

160
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:53,360
And I don't feel ready.

161
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:57,160
I think I want to build
my own financial stability first.

162
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,040
Then I'll think about dating.

163
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:04,160
Hey! You sound just like Peace.

164
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:06,800
When he met my dad,
he said the exact same thing.

165
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:08,080
But back then,

166
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:11,560
he already had hundreds of millions,
so my dad loved him so much.

167
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,800
My dad is totally money-minded.
Just saying.

168
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,880
My dad says he raised me well.

169
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:19,640
If I bring home
a boyfriend with no future,

170
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,320
he'll never approve it.

171
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:26,480
Do you agree with your dad?

172
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,040
No.

173
00:12:29,560 --> 00:12:32,360
But I read on Twitter. They said,

174
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:34,800
"When poverty comes in through the door,

175
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,520
love flies out the window."

176
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,600
I think that's true. Someone who's ready

177
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:41,560
is just better, right? Don't you think?

178
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:44,920
Yeah.

179
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:47,720
Miss Franc, should I take this
inside for you?

180
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,840
Oh.

181
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:53,280
Here, take this. This one's really good.

182
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,280
You sent the driver to Yaowarat for this?

183
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,840
Yeah, I was craving it.

184
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,560
I'm off now. Get home safely.

185
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,920
See you. Bye.

186
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,840
Usually, their income isn't stable.

187
00:13:13,920 --> 00:13:17,440
They usually do
daily wage jobs, general labor,

188
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:20,360
selling goods, street vending,

189
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:22,480
and food carts.

190
00:13:22,560 --> 00:13:25,120
This one is called a food cart,

191
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:28,920
whereas hawkers carry their goods
and keep moving around.

192
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,360
Cool.

193
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:37,160
I'm sure the vendors
would call it tiring, not cool.

194
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:41,600
It's an independent job
that reaches customers at their doorstep.

195
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:44,000
That's even more advanced than delivery.

196
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,320
If we can change how people see it,

197
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,600
this job will become really valuable.

198
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:50,200
It's like an app in Indonesia

199
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:53,280
that started because of
their severe traffic,

200
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:55,440
making people turn to motorcycle taxis.

201
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:59,560
The app founders went out
into the field just like us.

202
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:03,400
Then they built an app
to help motorcycle taxi drivers earn more.

203
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:05,040
Even regular people

204
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,680
started becoming motorcycle taxi riders
to earn money.

205
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,360
Why are you smiling?

206
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:17,320
Well, today

207
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,120
you've been talking a lot.

208
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,880
Usually, you just give short answers.

209
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,680
When you give orders, it's always brief.

210
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:25,880
But today

211
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:29,760
you've been talking
really, really, really long.

212
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,640
That means we're close now, right?

213
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,600
Right?

214
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,160
Are we? We are, right?

215
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,880
Why are you getting shy?

216
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,040
What's up, Ken?

217
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,160
Cent! We've got a big problem.

218
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:53,200
The payment gateway is down.

219
00:14:53,280 --> 00:14:55,600
Everything here is a mess, Cent.

220
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:57,400
<i>We need to fix it now.</i>

221
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,680
Got it. I'll take a look.

222
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,080
Wait.

223
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,320
Today there are idol ticket sales, right?

224
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:06,360
Yes.

225
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:11,000
People are probably frustrated
and hitting refresh nonstop.

226
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:13,920
Traffic spikes, bandwidth maxes out.
More issues will follow.

227
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,520
I'll increase the bandwidth
and scale out the system.

228
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,960
Tell the payment gateway team
to clear the system and handle the basics.

229
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,480
I'll handle the system fix.

230
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:33,800
What's going on?

231
00:15:33,880 --> 00:15:35,360
The payment gateway is down.

232
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:37,800
What does that mean?

233
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,600
It's like…

234
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:43,720
there's a road where all lanes
are completely jammed with cars

235
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,520
and nothing can move.

236
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:48,600
I have to add more lanes
to let the traffic flow again. Got it?

237
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:50,680
Yes.

238
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:55,960
Wow, that's just like clients
asking for graphic revisions.

239
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:57,760
Quiet! I need to focus.

240
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:15,800
Cent, I think we need
to increase the bandwidth.

241
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:19,080
We only recovered it for a short while,
and now it's down again.

242
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:23,000
Alright. I'll increase it threefold.

243
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:26,960
I just want to tell those ticket buyers
to stop refreshing!

244
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:31,360
Ken, go tell the team
to refactor that garbage code.

245
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:33,360
I just checked it. It's a mess!

246
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:35,200
It makes code cleanup so damn hard.

247
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,880
Fix it now!

248
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:21,200
Yes!

249
00:17:36,640 --> 00:17:38,560
Hey!

250
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:41,840
Hey! Like this?

251
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,880
Do it like this?

252
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,400
Yuan.

253
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,040
How's work at your uncle's factory?

254
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,440
It's okay, Dad.

255
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:35,680
Any problems?

256
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:36,760
No.

257
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:39,600
But…

258
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:44,560
It's just a fixed salary, Dad.
I want another source of income.

259
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:48,360
What do you want to do?

260
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,520
Well.

261
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,960
Something we're good at as a family.

262
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:54,800
Like starting our own clothing brand.

263
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:57,560
I design it, you and Mom produce it.

264
00:18:57,640 --> 00:18:59,000
The whole family earns together.

265
00:18:59,080 --> 00:18:59,920
Nonsense!

266
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,440
Easy for you to say.

267
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:05,200
But it's not easy in reality.
With design work,

268
00:19:05,280 --> 00:19:07,560
doing it isn't worth the cost.

269
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,520
Designers work insanely hard,
only for everything to get copied.

270
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:14,040
You've seen it yourself.
Customers would come to us,

271
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:17,680
show photos on their phones,
and ask us to make it.

272
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:18,920
Something worth tens of thousands

273
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,280
go down to just a few thousand.

274
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:23,920
Dad's right. Why exhaust yourself
doing your own thing?

275
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:26,000
Just take the salary from your uncle.

276
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:29,920
Focus on your job.
He will hand the factory over to you.

277
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,000
He doesn't have a wife or kids.

278
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:33,960
He's relying on you two.

279
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:37,960
But if you don't try, you'll never know.
I want to try.

280
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:39,560
No trying!

281
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:42,680
Waste of time!
Focus on working for your uncle.

282
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:44,520
And you'd better not do it behind my back.

283
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:51,440
Here, eat this.
Your uncle sent all this good food.

284
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,160
Eat it and be grateful to him.

285
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,400
Yuan, what's going on?

286
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,480
Why do you want to find another job?

287
00:20:20,440 --> 00:20:21,800
Do you not like factory work?

288
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:23,720
It's not that.

289
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:25,920
I can do the work,

290
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,720
but I want to get rich fast.

291
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:32,480
Are you in debt?
Did you do something illegal?

292
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:33,560
No!

293
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,360
I just want money to impress a girl.

294
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:41,280
Without money, it's hard to date.

295
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:43,840
Hey, that's nonsense.

296
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:47,160
If a girl only likes you for money,
then don't go for her.

297
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:51,040
It's not like that. Just…

298
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:56,600
I want to get rich fast
and have something of my own, that's all.

299
00:20:58,360 --> 00:20:59,600
I get it.

300
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,600
When I graduated, I felt the same.

301
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:05,600
But after working with Uncle,
I stopped thinking like that.

302
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:09,040
Because one day,
he'll hand the factory over to us.

303
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,960
Uncle and Dad are counting on us a lot.

304
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,800
Don't go causing trouble, alright?

305
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:19,800
Okay.

306
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,800
You're just like Dad.

307
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,400
Got everything? Didn't forget anything?

308
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,200
Nope, all good.

309
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:47,920
Are you going to hang out
with me and my friends today?

310
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:53,160
Better not. I signed up for the IC exam,
and it's coming up soon.

311
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:54,640
I need to study.

312
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:59,640
Babe, you go and have fun. Okay?

313
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,800
I want you to come with me.

314
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,000
I really can't.

315
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:12,960
Fine. But after your exam,
you're not allowed to bail on me.

316
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,480
Okay, I promise.

317
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,400
Let's go.

318
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:20,880
Hurry home. Traffic's going to be bad.

319
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:23,000
Next time, you have to come with me.

320
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:26,800
Okay, sure.

321
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:27,960
-Hey.
-Huh?

322
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:30,720
How are you getting home?
Is your car fixed yet?

323
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:33,440
Yeah, it's fixed.
They said they'll bring it here.

324
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:37,560
-Alright, okay.
-Yeah. Let's go.

325
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:40,640
Bye.

326
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,840
-Bye. Get home safe.
-Yes.

327
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:45,280
-Text me when you arrive.
-Okay.

328
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:09,960
I'm at J5 right now.

329
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,800
Where are you? Oh, okay.

330
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,160
Babe?

331
00:23:58,080 --> 00:23:59,000
Whose house is this?

332
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:01,280
My friend's house.

333
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:02,360
Your friend?

334
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,240
Which friend? Do I know them?

335
00:24:04,320 --> 00:24:05,040
-Who?
-Babe. Babe.

336
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:07,080
Babe, please go home first. Trust me.

337
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:09,040
And whose car was that just now?

338
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:11,280
Didn't you say your car was already fixed?

339
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:12,920
Why are you lying to me?

340
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:15,320
I'm not lying to you.

341
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:17,880
I'll explain everything later, Neng.

342
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:18,800
Just go home first.

343
00:24:18,880 --> 00:24:21,280
-Trust me.
-I'm not going! Whose house is this?

344
00:24:21,360 --> 00:24:23,160
-Tell me!
-Neng, trust me.

345
00:24:23,240 --> 00:24:24,880
-I said I'm not leaving!
-Just go home.

346
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:27,040
-I'm begging you. Please go home.
-No! Let me go!

347
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:28,960
-Just go home first.
-I'm not going!

348
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,000
-Just go home, please.
-Which friend? Tell me!

349
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:32,800
-Pound.
-I'm begging you.

350
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:33,680
-I'm not leaving!
-Pound.

351
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:35,280
Babe, please go--

352
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:41,800
I bought some food.
Let's have a family dinner.

353
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,680
I'll head inside the house.

354
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:57,520
Family? House?

355
00:24:58,160 --> 00:24:59,880
Why are you lying, Pound?

356
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:02,160
-You said you wouldn't lie!
-I'm not lying to you!

357
00:25:02,240 --> 00:25:03,640
Can you calm down first?

358
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:05,600
We're a couple, right?

359
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,240
Please trust me, babe. Go home first.

360
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:10,240
Because we're a couple,
we should be honest with each other.

361
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:13,600
How many times
have you lied to me already?

362
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:16,440
Huh?

363
00:25:17,040 --> 00:25:18,560
I've never lied to you, okay?

364
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,040
-Calm down.
-Think I'll believe that?

365
00:25:20,120 --> 00:25:21,760
You think I'll still believe you?

366
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,040
Fine!

367
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:26,440
Okay! Let me be honest with you then.

368
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:29,840
You're acting like this

369
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:32,440
because you're not okay with it, right?
My family went bankrupt.

370
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:34,800
We're not rich anymore,
and I can't support you like before.

371
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,080
You're embarrassed, aren't you?

372
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:38,400
This is what you think of me?

373
00:25:39,560 --> 00:25:42,800
You think I date guys for money?
That I only want rich men?

374
00:25:43,640 --> 00:25:45,040
Let me tell you.

375
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,400
I'm already rich!

376
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:48,920
I don't care about a man's money.

377
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:50,640
I just want honesty.

378
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:53,440
No lies, no pretending.
But you're exactly all of that!

379
00:25:57,680 --> 00:26:00,160
Babe, I'm sorry. I didn't mean it.

380
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,240
Enough. Stop it!

381
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:04,480
All the good feelings are gone.

382
00:26:05,240 --> 00:26:08,200
Go lie to whoever you want.
Go fool whoever you want. Go ahead!

383
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:12,880
But you can't lie to me anymore.
We're done.

384
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:16,240
-Babe, I'm sorry.
-Let go!

385
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,600
I don't want you anymore.

386
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:49,480
You can lie to anyone,

387
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:53,280
but you can't lie to yourself.

388
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:58,360
We're not rich anymore.

389
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:01,200
No one's giving you money now.

390
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:02,880
You have to accept it.

391
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:05,640
Otherwise, you'll go around
lying to people.

392
00:27:06,240 --> 00:27:09,200
And when you get caught,
it's embarrassing.

393
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,360
Why are you rubbing it in, Dad?

394
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:15,080
I'll keep repeating it until you wake up.

395
00:27:18,320 --> 00:27:22,520
Remember this. People
who are with us for benefits

396
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:24,640
will leave when we have nothing.

397
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:26,400
I've been through it many times.

398
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,720
When we were down and had no money,

399
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:33,960
all my friends disappeared.
Not a single one helped.

400
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,200
But my friends aren't like yours.

401
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:41,880
Do your friends
even know you've gone broke?

402
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:47,200
They don't, do they?

403
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,560
Yet you still act so confident.

404
00:27:52,880 --> 00:27:54,200
Remember this.

405
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:57,000
When we hit rock bottom,

406
00:27:58,080 --> 00:28:02,280
that's when we see people's true colors,

407
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:06,080
even our own children.

408
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:11,720
Yes.

409
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:15,920
This son of yours is bad.

410
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:19,080
He's evil. He's money-hungry.
He refuses to face reality.

411
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:23,480
But look at him carefully, Dad.

412
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:26,760
This son of yours

413
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:30,960
will make our family rich again.
Just wait and see.

414
00:28:31,840 --> 00:28:34,280
Pound!

415
00:28:34,360 --> 00:28:37,320
-Pound! Where are you going?
-Hey.

416
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:42,920
He won't go far.
He'll come back on his own.

417
00:28:44,400 --> 00:28:46,920
-I'll go get him to eat with us.
-Pung.

418
00:28:48,440 --> 00:28:49,480
We'll eat without him.

419
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:53,840
Don't mind that ungrateful son.

420
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:49,880
Pound, what's up?

421
00:29:51,880 --> 00:29:53,600
Hey, are you okay?

422
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:55,240
Don't lock up yet.

423
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:56,840
It's late already. Where are you going?

424
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:57,880
I'm going to see Pound.

425
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:01,600
Yeah, I'm heading out now.

426
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,760
Okay.

427
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:06,400
Hey, calm down.

428
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:09,160
Don't go anywhere yet.
I'll come to you after work.

429
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:11,160
That's it for now. Don't go anywhere.

430
00:30:12,360 --> 00:30:13,600
What's up with your friend this time?

431
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:15,920
Probably having problems
with his girlfriend and family.

432
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:19,440
But it's okay. I'll go see him after work.

433
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:23,240
Where is he? I'll drop you off.

434
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,320
Drop me off?

435
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,560
Hey, enough already.

436
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:31,840
-Hey! Bonus!
-I think you've had too much.

437
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,440
I'm fine.

438
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:36,840
Whoa, enough. This
is your last drink, okay?

439
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:37,840
That's it.

440
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:38,760
One more--

441
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:41,680
Hey, Pound! Don't puke, okay?

442
00:30:41,760 --> 00:30:43,000
Hold it in.

443
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:45,720
What do I do now?

444
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:46,960
Whoa.

445
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:49,480
Yuan, over here!

446
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:51,000
-Pound.
-This way.

447
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,440
-Why is he in this state?
-Hey!

448
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:57,480
I don't know. All I know
is he broke up with Nheng-Neng,

449
00:30:57,560 --> 00:30:59,400
ahen I got here, he kept drinking nonstop.

450
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,760
We should take him to my place.

451
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:01,760
I agree.

452
00:31:01,840 --> 00:31:03,720
-Let's go.
-I'm not going. Where are we going?

453
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:05,440
-Get up, Pound.
-Excuse me.

454
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:07,400
-Bill, please. This table!
-Let's go.

455
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,520
-I'll take you home.
-Pound.

456
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:10,880
-Careful, don't puke!
-Hey.

457
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:12,560
-Don't throw up.
-Don't.

458
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,840
-Hold it in. Hey, hurry up!
-Walk carefully.

459
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:16,000
-Bill, please!
-Careful, Pound.

460
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:18,360
-Check us out. This table!
-Uneven steps. Watch out.

461
00:31:23,360 --> 00:31:25,480
-Thank you, Cent.
-Yeah.

462
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,600
-Careful, take it slow.
-Pound!

463
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:44,680
-Pound!
-Ugh.

464
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:45,800
Walk slowly.

465
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,200
-Hey.
-Walk properly.

466
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:48,360
Don't collapse.

467
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,600
Yeah.

468
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:51,760
Hey, where are you guys going?

469
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:55,240
I'm taking him to my place.
Franc is paying. She'll come out later.

470
00:31:55,920 --> 00:31:56,840
-Hey.
-Hey!

471
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,920
-Fuang, my friend!
-Hey, Pound!

472
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:01,240
-Pound!
-Long time no see.

473
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:05,160
Pound!

474
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:07,560
I've got him.

475
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:09,400
Fuang, your phone.

476
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:11,120
Thank you.

477
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:13,960
-Hello, Cent.
-Hello.

478
00:32:14,040 --> 00:32:15,560
Cent is here!

479
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:17,760
-Hey.
-Hey, Pound!

480
00:32:17,840 --> 00:32:19,440
Hey!

481
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:22,960
Cent, hello.

482
00:32:25,240 --> 00:32:28,880
You always look so serious.

483
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:31,440
-Hey.
-Bill's settled, guys.

484
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:32,800
No!

485
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:35,440
What's going on? What happened?

486
00:32:40,480 --> 00:32:42,120
-Ew. Direct hit.
-Pound!

487
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:44,200
Pound!

488
00:32:48,520 --> 00:32:50,000
-You made a mess.
-Pound.

489
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,080
Pound.

490
00:32:59,960 --> 00:33:02,600
Warm ginger tea. It'll help you sober up.

491
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:08,400
Easy, Pound.

492
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:10,000
Here.

493
00:33:22,800 --> 00:33:26,280
Honestly, that puke moment
just now was gold.

494
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:28,400
So satisfying!

495
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,640
Sorry.

496
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:36,600
Where did Fuang and Cent go?

497
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,840
Fuang took my dad's shirt
for him to change.

498
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:41,440
They're probably in the bathroom.

499
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:47,200
Cent, I brought a bag for you.

500
00:33:58,280 --> 00:33:59,240
Hello, Dad.

501
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:02,640
Sorry.

502
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:06,440
You really look like Bonus's dad.

503
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:12,760
But you look good. Kinda vintage.

504
00:34:18,239 --> 00:34:19,280
Here's a bag.

505
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:27,120
Take your time, Dad. I mean, Cent.

506
00:34:28,360 --> 00:34:30,280
I'll go check on Pound.

507
00:34:42,719 --> 00:34:44,960
How's Pound… doing?

508
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,160
Pound.

509
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:03,080
What's going on?

510
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:09,160
He told us

511
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:13,120
why Nheng-Neng dumped him.

512
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:17,320
She found out

513
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:20,680
that he was lying.

514
00:35:22,680 --> 00:35:24,120
He didn't tell her

515
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:26,240
that his family went bankrupt.

516
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:32,160
Whoa, Pound.

517
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:35,120
His house got seized.

518
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:37,400
They had to move into a rental.

519
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:39,480
His dad sold the car.

520
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:42,080
Now he's got nothing left.

521
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,960
Just let it out.

522
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:50,360
Go ahead and cry. I'm fine.

523
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:56,840
How long has this been going on?

524
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:59,280
A while now.

525
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:02,080
Before Bonus even opened the shop.

526
00:36:03,160 --> 00:36:04,720
Huh? Hey.

527
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:10,360
Then where did you get
the money to fund me?

528
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:14,120
I…

529
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:17,080
I sold my designer stuff.

530
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:19,720
-Pound.
-Pound.

531
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:23,240
I got some money from that
and gave it to you.

532
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:26,840
Why didn't you tell me?

533
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:40,960
I was scared.

534
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:47,360
I was scared that if I told you guys…

535
00:36:51,760 --> 00:36:53,600
you'd stop being friends with me.

536
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:55,440
-Hey.
-Pound.

537
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:56,440
Pound.

538
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:57,880
Why'd you think that?

539
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:58,920
What makes you think that?

540
00:36:59,000 --> 00:36:59,840
Yeah.

541
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:02,800
I don't know.

542
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:06,120
We've known each other since kindergarten.

543
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:09,040
Back when we didn't even know
what rich or poor meant.

544
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:11,120
Our friendship

545
00:37:11,200 --> 00:37:13,560
has nothing to do with money.

546
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:16,840
It doesn't matter if you're rich or poor.

547
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:18,680
Friends

548
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:22,240
aren't just for hanging out or partying.

549
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:25,840
Stop thinking like that.

550
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:29,640
We're not gonna stop
being friends with you because of that.

551
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:31,200
It has nothing to do with it.

552
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:36,280
If there's anything
I can help with, just tell me.

553
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:38,720
If I can help, I will do my best.

554
00:37:39,520 --> 00:37:40,520
As for me,

555
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,520
I don't have many friends.

556
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:44,760
I'm not gonna leave you, man.

557
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,640
Come here.

558
00:37:52,360 --> 00:37:54,800
Thanks.

559
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,480
Thank you so much, guys.

560
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,520
-Pound.
-What?

561
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:09,920
We'll get rich together, remember?

562
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:12,480
We'll get rich together!

563
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:15,880
-Yeah!
-We'll get rich together!

564
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:18,920
Okay.

565
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:26,200
Your boss image is gone.

566
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:30,320
-Hey, he's smiling now.
-Our boss Pound.

567
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:46,880
Cent.

568
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:50,880
It's raining, so I brought you
an umbrella.

569
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:53,320
Thanks.

570
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:57,440
I'm sorry on Pound's behalf.

571
00:38:58,320 --> 00:39:00,320
It's fine. He was drunk.

572
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:03,640
He isn't usually like that.

573
00:39:03,720 --> 00:39:05,400
He's just going through a rough time,

574
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:07,280
so he's a bit down.

575
00:39:08,480 --> 00:39:09,440
Thanks.

576
00:39:12,280 --> 00:39:13,440
For what?

577
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,640
For finding me
an umbrella and a fan earlier.

578
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,360
Oh.

579
00:39:18,440 --> 00:39:21,760
Huge umbrella, tiny fan.

580
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:25,080
That was the biggest one
I could find at the time.

581
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:30,880
You looked really stressed earlier.

582
00:39:31,520 --> 00:39:33,040
So stressed, you didn't even see me.

583
00:39:33,120 --> 00:39:35,000
But I understand.

584
00:39:35,080 --> 00:39:38,040
When I was taking graphic jobs,
I felt like that too.

585
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:43,280
Oh, right. You still have work
to go back and finish.

586
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:46,080
I'll just stay up all night.
I'm used to it.

587
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:51,520
What about the work we have tomorrow?

588
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:53,320
Tomorrow…

589
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,240
morning's cancelled.
See you in the evening.

590
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:56,600
I'll pick you up at your place.

591
00:39:57,600 --> 00:39:59,360
-It's okay.
-Why do I have to repeat myself?

592
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:01,200
I said I'll pick you up.

593
00:40:03,080 --> 00:40:04,320
Okay.

594
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:07,840
You don't have to be so harsh.

595
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:11,000
Fine. I'll say it again.

596
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:16,560
Why do I have to repeat myself?
I said I'll pick you up, okay?

597
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:20,440
So fake.

598
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:24,840
You're not sincere at all.

599
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:29,480
That's it. I'm going.

600
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:43,320
See you at my house tomorrow.

601
00:40:51,760 --> 00:40:54,080
Are you really okay working with Cent?

602
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:59,400
It's work. Of course, there are problems,

603
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,680
but they're problems I can handle.

604
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:06,160
Working while solving problems
is actually kind of fun.

605
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:10,960
Have you had time to do your own work?
I only see you busy with his stuff.

606
00:41:12,480 --> 00:41:13,520
Not yet.

607
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:18,280
But Cent's job pays, so it comes first.

608
00:41:18,880 --> 00:41:21,000
As for my passion work,

609
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:22,840
it can wait.

610
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:26,920
Thanks for worrying about me.

611
00:41:28,240 --> 00:41:32,160
Honestly, Cent isn't as bad as you think.

612
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:34,840
If you got to know him like I do,

613
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:37,240
you'd see he's actually a good person.

614
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:56,800
<i>Human feelings can change anytime.</i>

615
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:59,680
<i>Today you hate someone,</i>
<i>tomorrow you might love them.</i>

616
00:42:00,800 --> 00:42:02,720
<i>From feeling indifferent,</i>

617
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:05,800
<i>it might turn into something special.</i>

618
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:08,560
<i>From hopelessness,</i>

619
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:10,840
<i>it starts turning into hope.</i>

620
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,360
<i>From pity</i>

621
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:17,760
<i>and sympathy,</i>

622
00:42:18,960 --> 00:42:21,920
<i>it becomes love.</i>

623
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:33,120
<i>Ever since Peace left and went far away,</i>

624
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:37,440
<i>I've gone through</i>
<i>constantly changing emotions.</i>

625
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:40,920
<i>My sadness slowly turned into happiness.</i>

626
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,400
<i>It made me realize</i>

627
00:42:43,480 --> 00:42:47,000
<i>life still has so much for us</i>
<i>to go out and discover.</i>

628
00:42:47,080 --> 00:42:50,800
<i>Peace, If you are watching this</i>
<i>from somewhere far away,</i>

629
00:42:50,880 --> 00:42:52,560
<i>I want you to know</i>

630
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:55,600
<i>I'm about to start</i>
<i>following my own dream now.</i>

631
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:59,360
<i>Even though we were separated</i>
<i>without a goodbye,</i>

632
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:02,960
<i>I will never forget the good times</i>
<i>we had together.</i>

633
00:43:03,520 --> 00:43:06,320
<i>And one day, I'll come find you.</i>

634
00:43:10,680 --> 00:43:13,320
Franc!

635
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,680
Have you seen your video's views on IG?

636
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,360
Look, it even got reposted on Twitter.

637
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:21,120
So many people love it, Franc.

638
00:43:23,480 --> 00:43:26,080
Oh no, Franc! I'm sorry.

639
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:28,760
I didn't know you were crying.

640
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:29,960
It's okay, Franc. Peace--

641
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:32,360
No, I'm happy.

642
00:43:32,440 --> 00:43:35,480
The views are doing so well!

643
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:39,280
People are accepting that I've moved on.

644
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:41,680
If I start my YouTube channel,
no one will hate me,

645
00:43:41,760 --> 00:43:45,400
and the people who looked down on me,
they'll see that I can do it.

646
00:43:45,480 --> 00:43:47,320
Oh.

647
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:49,080
Oh, okay.

648
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:51,880
Look at the comments.

649
00:43:53,160 --> 00:43:55,040
Hey, look.

650
00:43:59,120 --> 00:44:00,240
So many comments.

651
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:05,600
Franc's right.

652
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:07,520
People have to move on in life.

653
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:12,160
How are you gonna move on?

654
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:17,080
I'm going to take the IC exam.

655
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:19,480
What's that?

656
00:44:19,560 --> 00:44:21,480
A stockbroker license.

657
00:44:21,560 --> 00:44:23,080
If I pass,

658
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:26,080
I'll start finding clients
and trading stocks as well.

659
00:44:30,920 --> 00:44:31,920
I'm…

660
00:44:34,040 --> 00:44:35,720
I'm sorry.

661
00:44:38,120 --> 00:44:40,800
I really didn't know
you were going through all this.

662
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:43,840
I've spent so much of your money.

663
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:47,040
Hey, don't overthink it.

664
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:48,760
I already promised you.

665
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:50,400
Even if I go broke,

666
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:53,040
I'll still find a way
to invest in your shop.

667
00:44:58,840 --> 00:45:01,280
I'll do my best.

668
00:45:02,320 --> 00:45:05,720
So your parents will see
you invested in the right person.

669
00:45:12,920 --> 00:45:14,360
That's more like it.

670
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:27,920
When you two went from friends to lovers,

671
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:30,600
how did it feel? Were you scared?

672
00:45:32,280 --> 00:45:35,400
At first, I was scared
that he wouldn't be the same,

673
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:37,240
but he wasn't at all.

674
00:45:37,320 --> 00:45:39,680
He's always been consistent.

675
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:42,800
How he was as a friend,
he's the same as a boyfriend.

676
00:45:42,880 --> 00:45:44,800
In fact, he even makes me feel better.

677
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:47,480
Look at you.

678
00:45:47,560 --> 00:45:49,840
What about you, Dad? Were you scared?

679
00:45:49,920 --> 00:45:51,360
-I was.
-Huh?

680
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:54,480
I was scared
that if I didn't cross that line quickly,

681
00:45:54,560 --> 00:45:57,840
your mom would go to someone else.
She was really hot back then, you know.

682
00:45:57,920 --> 00:46:00,960
I'm still hot now. Eat this.

683
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:03,520
Did you ever think,

684
00:46:04,080 --> 00:46:06,560
if one day you broke up,

685
00:46:06,640 --> 00:46:08,080
it would feel

686
00:46:08,160 --> 00:46:09,920
like losing your best friend?

687
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:14,880
No, because I never planned to break up.

688
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:15,920
Wow.

689
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:16,800
But I did.

690
00:46:16,880 --> 00:46:17,760
-Huh?
-What?

691
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:20,160
It did cross my mind sometimes.

692
00:46:20,240 --> 00:46:22,640
-Oh.
-Fuang.

693
00:46:23,280 --> 00:46:25,800
Every relationship has risks.

694
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:29,320
Being friends first
doesn't mean it will always work out.

695
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:33,760
That's true. We never know
what will happen

696
00:46:33,840 --> 00:46:36,760
in the future, whether it'll bring
happiness or sadness.

697
00:46:36,840 --> 00:46:38,360
Sometimes you have to take the risk.

698
00:46:38,440 --> 00:46:40,360
Yeah.

699
00:46:40,440 --> 00:46:44,920
-Hey! Why are you asking this?
-Yes?

700
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:46,240
Don't tell me

701
00:46:46,920 --> 00:46:48,560
you've got a crush on a friend.

702
00:46:49,280 --> 00:46:50,760
-Huh?
-No!

703
00:46:50,840 --> 00:46:51,840
Really? Seriously?

704
00:46:51,920 --> 00:46:54,160
I was just asking. I'm not into anyone.

705
00:46:54,240 --> 00:46:56,560
-Seriously?
-Really? Tell us now.

706
00:46:56,640 --> 00:46:57,520
I really don't.

707
00:46:57,600 --> 00:46:58,760
-You sure?
-Sure!

708
00:46:58,840 --> 00:46:59,680
How long has it been?

709
00:46:59,760 --> 00:47:01,160
I said no!

710
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:03,680
Even if there is, that person isn't me.

711
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:04,640
Who?

712
00:47:04,720 --> 00:47:05,920
-Then who?
-Who?

713
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:07,240
Not telling.

714
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:09,480
Tell me now. Come on.

715
00:47:09,560 --> 00:47:11,560
Seriously, you've been
dating for a while, right?

716
00:47:11,640 --> 00:47:13,400
-No, Dad!
-Do you like him a lot?

717
00:47:13,480 --> 00:47:16,680
-You're blushing.
-No.

718
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,080
Yong, what's up?

719
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:32,000
This sketchbook.

720
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:36,840
Are you really planning
to start your own clothing brand?

721
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:40,160
All those times you took leave
and left early, was it for this?

722
00:47:42,200 --> 00:47:43,360
No.

723
00:47:43,440 --> 00:47:45,240
This is Fuang's sketchbook.

724
00:47:45,320 --> 00:47:46,680
She left it behind.

725
00:47:46,760 --> 00:47:49,560
I was planning to return it.

726
00:47:49,640 --> 00:47:50,760
Yuan.

727
00:47:52,720 --> 00:47:53,880
I told you already, didn't I?

728
00:47:55,360 --> 00:47:56,840
About what Uncle wants us to do

729
00:47:57,760 --> 00:47:59,560
and how much he's done for our family.

730
00:47:59,640 --> 00:48:02,800
Don't make me repeat myself.
We're adults now.

731
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:05,200
Yes.

732
00:48:24,200 --> 00:48:26,320
Does Yong even believe you?

733
00:48:26,400 --> 00:48:28,720
I don't know. From now on,
I'll have to do it secretly.

734
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:30,320
Otherwise, I'm in trouble for sure.

735
00:48:30,920 --> 00:48:31,880
Hey.

736
00:48:33,200 --> 00:48:36,040
Franc has already moved on from Peace.

737
00:48:36,120 --> 00:48:38,520
This is your chance. Wanna go for it?

738
00:48:39,440 --> 00:48:40,640
No.

739
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:41,640
What?

740
00:48:42,240 --> 00:48:44,360
Why not? Don't tell me

741
00:48:44,440 --> 00:48:46,200
you're worried you're not rich enough.

742
00:48:46,280 --> 00:48:48,160
I kind of tested it with Franc.

743
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:52,480
And basically,
her dad doesn't like poor guys.

744
00:48:54,360 --> 00:48:56,160
He's afraid they can't
take care of his daughter.

745
00:49:05,240 --> 00:49:07,720
Honestly, her dad's not wrong.

746
00:49:09,560 --> 00:49:11,680
He raised her well.

747
00:49:12,280 --> 00:49:14,520
Of course he wants someone ready
to take care of her,

748
00:49:14,600 --> 00:49:16,760
but I don't want you to lose hope.

749
00:49:16,840 --> 00:49:19,920
Someday, you might be ready for her too.

750
00:49:21,880 --> 00:49:23,800
Don't give up, Yuan.

751
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:28,560
Nick, do you think it's Yuan

752
00:49:28,640 --> 00:49:30,720
she's about to cross the line with?

753
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:34,560
Huh?

754
00:49:34,640 --> 00:49:37,080
Maybe not.

755
00:49:44,920 --> 00:49:46,080
Return the shirt.

756
00:49:47,040 --> 00:49:48,240
Hello, Cent.

757
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:52,920
Done with the drawing lesson yet?

758
00:49:53,640 --> 00:49:56,320
We've got work to do. I'll wait outside.

759
00:49:56,400 --> 00:49:57,520
Okay.

760
00:49:59,800 --> 00:50:03,240
Keep it up. You're doing great.
I have to go to work now.

761
00:50:03,320 --> 00:50:05,960
Cent seemed kind of stressed today.

762
00:50:06,040 --> 00:50:07,960
I think he looked
more jealous than stressed.

763
00:50:11,480 --> 00:50:13,880
Hey! What are you talking about?

764
00:50:13,960 --> 00:50:14,960
Stop talking nonsense.

765
00:50:15,040 --> 00:50:17,800
You're getting hit on by a nerd.

766
00:50:17,880 --> 00:50:20,440
But I think Cent is actually okay.

767
00:50:20,520 --> 00:50:22,480
I've met him three to four times.

768
00:50:22,560 --> 00:50:24,600
He seems cool, straightforward,

769
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:26,640
kind of unpredictable.

770
00:50:26,720 --> 00:50:28,080
He suits you.

771
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:33,280
What are you talking about?
What do you mean?

772
00:50:37,720 --> 00:50:39,000
I can't really explain it.

773
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:41,600
But he and you

774
00:50:41,680 --> 00:50:44,240
have some kind of chemistry.
Something like that.

775
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:45,520
And

776
00:50:46,160 --> 00:50:49,920
when you're with him, you're more natural.
You seem like yourself.

777
00:50:50,640 --> 00:50:52,600
I'm natural when I'm with you too.

778
00:50:52,680 --> 00:50:55,080
Oh! Your cheeks are pink.

779
00:50:55,160 --> 00:50:56,720
Your shirt's pink.

780
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:58,240
-Your pants are pink.
-Yuan!

781
00:50:58,320 --> 00:51:00,880
-Yuan!
-Why is everything so pink?

782
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:02,640
Geez.

783
00:51:13,200 --> 00:51:15,080
Do you get jobs through apps,

784
00:51:15,160 --> 00:51:17,360
or do you only work here?

785
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:20,160
I use every app.
I've got uniforms in every color.

786
00:51:20,240 --> 00:51:21,760
Has your income increased?

787
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:23,600
It has, but it's tiring.

788
00:51:24,200 --> 00:51:26,640
Sometimes customers
send me really far away.

789
00:51:26,720 --> 00:51:28,080
It takes almost the whole day.

790
00:51:28,160 --> 00:51:31,120
Short local rides are better.
I can do more trips.

791
00:51:31,200 --> 00:51:33,880
Let's say I have a service for you to try.

792
00:51:33,960 --> 00:51:36,040
Short-distance deliveries
within the community.

793
00:51:36,120 --> 00:51:39,160
Fewer trips, but higher pay.
Would you be interested?

794
00:51:39,240 --> 00:51:42,280
Of course. Who wouldn't want more money?

795
00:51:51,160 --> 00:51:52,040
What are you drawing?

796
00:51:57,160 --> 00:51:59,040
I'm drawing him.

797
00:51:59,600 --> 00:52:02,760
Visual data helps me remember better.

798
00:52:05,160 --> 00:52:07,200
Yeah, that's good.

799
00:52:09,200 --> 00:52:10,440
Save his number too.

800
00:52:11,720 --> 00:52:12,680
Yes.

801
00:52:25,880 --> 00:52:26,720
Excuse me.

802
00:52:26,800 --> 00:52:28,560
Can I get your phone number?

803
00:52:28,640 --> 00:52:29,800
What are you looking at?

804
00:52:30,680 --> 00:52:32,240
Fuang's boss.

805
00:52:32,880 --> 00:52:34,240
He's so handsome.

806
00:52:36,440 --> 00:52:38,000
He's so artsy,

807
00:52:38,080 --> 00:52:40,920
cool, and quiet.

808
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:44,320
I really like it. Do you know him?

809
00:52:47,200 --> 00:52:48,440
I've met him before.

810
00:52:49,520 --> 00:52:51,440
He's just okay. Nothing special.

811
00:52:52,160 --> 00:52:55,400
Franc, if you ever get
to meet Fuang's boss again,

812
00:52:55,480 --> 00:52:57,560
tell me, okay? I want to meet him.

813
00:52:57,640 --> 00:52:59,240
It's that serious?

814
00:53:00,120 --> 00:53:02,960
Your standards are low.
He's super handsome.

815
00:53:04,120 --> 00:53:07,480
-I really like him.
-You're obsessed with guys.

816
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:09,960
So handsome.

817
00:53:25,560 --> 00:53:26,760
<i>Honestly,</i>

818
00:53:26,840 --> 00:53:29,360
<i>Cent isn't as bad as you think.</i>

819
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:32,360
<i>If you got to know him like I do,</i>

820
00:53:32,440 --> 00:53:34,760
<i>you'd see he's actually a good person.</i>

821
00:53:42,360 --> 00:53:44,560
Just pick up. Don't overthink it.

822
00:53:46,280 --> 00:53:48,360
Thank you. Just a sec.

823
00:53:51,520 --> 00:53:52,440
What's up?

824
00:53:52,520 --> 00:53:53,400
<i>Hey.</i>

825
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:56,360
About the logo for my YouTube channel,
are you done yet?

826
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:58,720
<i>Don't tell me you forgot.</i>

827
00:53:59,240 --> 00:54:00,320
No, I didn't forget.

828
00:54:00,400 --> 00:54:02,280
You only gave me the channel name.

829
00:54:02,360 --> 00:54:04,000
You haven't sent me any references,

830
00:54:04,080 --> 00:54:05,840
so I don't know what style you want.

831
00:54:05,920 --> 00:54:08,800
Wait, I have to find references too?

832
00:54:09,400 --> 00:54:11,080
<i>I thought you could just design it.</i>

833
00:54:13,320 --> 00:54:14,200
One sec.

834
00:54:17,240 --> 00:54:21,000
It's doable, but it might not match
what you want.

835
00:54:21,080 --> 00:54:24,360
Just give me a rough concept of your show.

836
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:26,960
Also, send me logo references,

837
00:54:27,040 --> 00:54:28,920
colors, fonts, and typography details.

838
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:31,040
Tell me everything
so we don't need so many revisions.

839
00:54:31,120 --> 00:54:32,840
Okay, got it.

840
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:36,400
Hey, where are you right now?

841
00:54:37,120 --> 00:54:38,880
I might drop by
and show you the references.

842
00:54:41,520 --> 00:54:42,600
Hey, I've got to go.

843
00:54:42,680 --> 00:54:46,160
Send the references in the chat.
I'll check them. That's it. Bye.

844
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:50,040
Fuang!

845
00:54:56,280 --> 00:54:58,840
She's really determined.

846
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:02,080
She's planning to change her image

847
00:55:02,160 --> 00:55:04,240
and move on from Peace's drama.

848
00:55:04,320 --> 00:55:06,720
And soon, she's going to be
an actual YouTuber.

849
00:55:13,960 --> 00:55:15,440
Is something wrong?

850
00:55:18,480 --> 00:55:19,520
No.

851
00:55:21,040 --> 00:55:22,120
No?

852
00:55:23,600 --> 00:55:25,360
Yeah, nothing.

853
00:55:28,840 --> 00:55:30,440
Okay then. Nothing it is.

854
00:55:31,320 --> 00:55:32,240
Actually, there is.

855
00:55:33,520 --> 00:55:36,440
Your friends always bring you problems.
Don't you get tired of it?

856
00:55:39,640 --> 00:55:42,240
That's very direct.

857
00:55:43,280 --> 00:55:46,920
You're busy with your friends all day,
helping one or the other.

858
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:48,440
Don't you get tired, Fuang?

859
00:55:50,800 --> 00:55:52,600
You think it's tiring

860
00:55:53,160 --> 00:55:55,320
because you only see the bad moments.

861
00:55:57,120 --> 00:56:00,920
In reality, there are more good moments.

862
00:56:02,200 --> 00:56:05,960
We've known each other since we were kids.
We talk every day.

863
00:56:07,640 --> 00:56:09,840
Without them, I'd feel lonely.

864
00:56:11,200 --> 00:56:13,120
Aunt Eiang said
you don't have many friends.

865
00:56:13,200 --> 00:56:14,240
Don't you get lonely?

866
00:56:18,400 --> 00:56:20,720
Hiring a friend doesn't mean
you can talk down to them

867
00:56:20,800 --> 00:56:22,680
or say whatever you want to.

868
00:56:22,760 --> 00:56:25,840
Bonus, you're being dramatic.
Fuang hasn't even said anything.

869
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:27,600
She's not, so I have to speak for her.

870
00:56:27,680 --> 00:56:29,560
You can't just stay quiet, can you?

871
00:56:33,080 --> 00:56:33,960
Fuang.

872
00:56:35,680 --> 00:56:36,600
Yes?

873
00:56:36,680 --> 00:56:39,680
He seems really determined,
so I'd rather give the spot to him.

874
00:56:43,240 --> 00:56:44,080
Thank you.

875
00:56:44,800 --> 00:56:46,000
Hey, you don't have to bow.

876
00:56:46,080 --> 00:56:47,160
It looks just like you.

877
00:56:48,040 --> 00:56:49,920
Yeah, it's cute. I like this one.

878
00:56:50,000 --> 00:56:51,920
Even if no one likes it, I like it.

879
00:56:54,560 --> 00:56:58,920
Mee Boon even got you a guy.
Perfect timing.

880
00:56:59,600 --> 00:57:01,640
Don't mess it up, girl!

881
00:57:42,880 --> 00:57:47,560
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
